163.1	Panopticon	Panopticon	The Panopticon is a type of institutional building designed by English philosopher and social theorist Jeremy Bentham in the late eighteenth century. The concept of the design is to allow an observer to observe all (pan-) inmates of an institution without them being able to tell whether or not they are being watched.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/11/Panopticon.jpg/220px-Panopticon.jpg
